children.text: The Cognitive Diary is a technique used by cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT) to help with changing the irrational thinking that can contribute to various life problems such as anxiety, anger, depression, and relationship issues.

Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) provides concrete, specific methods to help change self-defeating behavior patterns and attitudes. Many problems can be addressed or improved by using these methods.
